        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/c5a1d2/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-20T03:21:49.691Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I can confirm that just now after turning on my smartphone for the first time in months that it spent a very long time downloading messages way older than 14 days.  Perhaps the 14 day retention period is not applying to messages not yet delivered to the primary device?</p>\n<p>I am not a smartphone user.  I turn this smartphone on only a few times per year, when Signal warns me in the desktop app that my account is at risk of termination.</p>",
