        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/c5a1d2/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-20T11:54:45.405Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Ok, this speaks to the heart of the problem I am having and why this feature request is valid â€“ I understand that if I want to stop message delivery to a linked device then I can just unlink and re-link it, but there is no way to stop delivery to the primary device.  This means that in practice, for anybody with a use case like mine (smartphone averse), there will always be 45 days worth of messages hanging around on Signal servers, when these messages for all practical intents and purposes are unwanted and already delivered.</p>\n<p>Ideally, it would be possible to change the primary device to a Desktop app instance.  But if there is some ideological reason why that canâ€™t be done, the next best solution would be to make delivery to the primary device configurable.</p>",
